experience_text:
experience
Data Analyst
Bakkt LLC-Alpharetta, GA
January 2021 to December 2024
• Write and optimize complex SQL queries using SQL (PL/SQL) to extract and manipulate large datasets
efficiently.
• Extract, cleanse, and validate financial claims data using Python, ensuring data accuracy and integrity
in the process.
• Analyze data to identify key metrics, trends, and patterns, providing insights for business
improvements.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including business analysts and other specialists, to gather
requirements and translate them into actionable data solutions.
• Leverage in-depth knowledge of financial and claims data to proactively address data-related
challenges and issues.
• Engage in data modeling activities to support the development and refinement of database structures,
improving system performance and ensuring scalability.
• Continuously assess current data processes and implement optimizations to enhance workflow
efficiency, reducing time and costs for data operations.
Order/Scheduling Manager
KEHE Distribution Center-Lithia Springs, GA
October 2017 to May 2021
• Supported the collection and analysis of product requirements from various departments, assisting
senior analysts in translating business needs into system capabilities.
• Helped create use cases, process flows, and user-interface schematics under the guidance of senior
team members.
• Assisted in extracting and analyzing data using SQL and Excel, generating reports and insights to inform
decision-making.
• Utilized Python to clean and preprocess raw customer data, ensuring it was ready for analysis and
reporting.
• worked closely with the senior data analysts to understand the needs of various departments and help
translate those into effective data strategies.
• Contributed to the documentation of system requirements and technical specifications, ensuring that
all deliverables met quality standards.
• Participated in internal meetings with stakeholders to gather feedback and clarify requirements for
software solutions.
• Managed comprehensive event data input into the Advanced Order Management system, ensuring
precise store ship order allocations and maintaining real-time shipment tracking to enhance supply chain
visibility.
• Delivered analytical support to the Customer Supply Chain team, contributing to informed decision-
making and operational efficiency improvements.
• Processed inventory disposition with a focus on accuracy, successfully meeting event-based customer
service level targets and maintaining a record of 100% accuracy in the Advanced Order Management
system.
